{"id":"1208.3517","submitter":"G\\'abor Cz\\'edli","authors":"G\\'abor Cz\\'edli","title":"Coordinatization of join-distributive lattices","comments":"20 pages, no figure","journal-ref":"Algebra Universalis 71, 385-404 (2014)","doi":"10.1007/s00012-014-0282-3","report-no":null,"categories":"math.RA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Join-distributive lattices are finite, meet-semidistributive, and semimodular\nlattices. They are the same as Dilworth's lattices in 1940, and many\nalternative definitions and equivalent concepts have been discovered or\nrediscovered since then. Let L be a join-distributive lattice of length n and\nlet k denote the width of the set of join-irreducible elements of L. A result\nof P.H. Edelman and R.E. Jamison, translated from Combinatorics to Lattice\nTheory, says that L can be described by k-1 permutations acting on the set\n{1,...,n}. We prove a similar result within Lattice Theory: there exist k-1\npermutations acting on {1,...,n} such that the elements of L are coordinatized\nby k-tuples over {0,...,n}, and the permutations determine which k-tuples are\nallowed. Since the concept of join-distributive lattices is equivalent to that\nof antimatroids and convex geometries, our result offers a coordinatization for\nthese combinatorial structures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 Aug 2012 01:27:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 9 Sep 2012 20:54:03 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 12 Oct 2012 12:32:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-18"}
